The NOR test was performed in the open field arena. On day 1, the mice were trained for 15 min with two identical objects placed near the periphery of the arena. One of the objects was then replaced by a different shape and color novel object 1 h after training, and the mice were allowed to explore the two objects for 15 min. Video tracking of the mice was analyzed offline by the experimenter to measure the time exploring each object. The mice were considered to be exploring if their head was directed at the object and they were sniffing it at a distance <1 cm. For training and the test session, a discrimination index (DI) was calculated using the equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
